Company Overview of Public Resources Advisory Group, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Public Resources Advisory Group, Inc. offers financial and investment advisory services. The company provides financial planning and advisory services in the areas of financing options evaluation; structuring issues; capital and financing plan development; refunding and restructuring analysis; credit analysis, rating agency presentation, and procurement of credit enhancement; debt affordability analysis; and cash flow analysis. It offers financing proposals review; feasibility analysis; revenue versus expenditure analysis; legal document review; procurement of underwriters and other bond professionals; and staff education and training. The company also offers debt issuance and management, in...
Public Resources Advisory Group, Inc. offers financial and investment advisory services. The company provides financial planning and advisory services in the areas of financing options evaluation; structuring issues; capital and financing plan development; refunding and restructuring analysis; credit analysis, rating agency presentation, and procurement of credit enhancement; debt affordability analysis; and cash flow analysis. It offers financing proposals review; feasibility analysis; revenue versus expenditure analysis; legal document review; procurement of underwriters and other bond professionals; and staff education and training. The company also offers debt issuance and management, including tax-exempt bonds, short-term and hedging products, taxable and structured debt and securitizations, and housing bonds. In addition, the company provides quantitative modeling and analytics, derivative and swap advisory, and investment advisory services. It serves state and local governments, authorities, agencies, and not-for-profit entities; and general municipal, transportation, public-private partnership, public power, environmental utility, higher education, economic development, and affordable housing industries in the United States. The company was founded in 1985 and is based in New York, New York with additional offices in Los Angeles and Oakland California; Philadelphia, Pennsylvania; and St. Petersburg, Florida.
