Mr. Peyser has been active in public finance since 1983 and manages the firm’s quantitative efforts, including reinvestment services and derivative product engagements. In addition, Mr. Peyser has been involved in analyzing the financing aspects of public-private partnerships for toll roads, sport facilities, resource recovery, utilities and economic development projects.  Mr. Peyser has significant expertise in structuring complex financings and in the negotiation of swap agreements with counterparties. He developed the firm’s methodology for real time swap and option pricing models. He is responsible for setting the firm’s standards for analysis and for assuring that the firm’s personnel have the proper tools to evaluate and implement financings. In addition, he serves as project manager on financings for a wide variety of purposes including general government, transportation, privatization, water and wastewater, and solid waste disposal and transactions involving derivative products.
Mr. Peyser holds a B.A. in Economics and History with Distinction in All Subjects from Cornell University and an M.B.A. in Finance from the Wharton School. He is a member of Phi Beta Kappa.
Show moreShow less



May Chau, Senior Managing Director
Certifications/Licenses: Series 50, Municipal Advisor Representative
Ms. Chau recently joined PRAG, bringing over 14 years of experience in municipal finance.  Prior to joining PRAG, Ms. Chau was an investment banker at Barclays where she covered municipal issuers in the Northeast and Mid-Atlantic regions. While at Barclays, Ms. Chau served as lead day-to-day banker for a number of transportation issuers, including the New York Metropolitan Transportation Authority, New Jersey Transportation Trust Fund Authority, New Jersey Transit Corporation, Georgia State Road and Tollway Authority, Metropolitan Atlanta Rapid Transit Authority and Miami International Airport.  Her other clients included the Virginia College Building Authority, State of New Jersey and New Jersey Economic Development Authority.  She also served in the Quantitative Group.  Prior to joining Barclays, Ms. Chau worked at DPC Data, Inc. and Thomson Financial Securities Data.
Ms. Chau holds a B.A. in Finance and MIS from the State University at Albany.
