Andrew Evanchik, Senior Managing Director
Certifications/Licenses: Series 50, Municipal Advisor Representative and
Series 65, Investment Advisor Representative
Mr. Evanchik provides quantitative analysis for the derivatives transactions of PRAG clients including the City of New York, the State of New York, the Empire State Development Corporation, LGAC, the Dormitory Authority of the State of New York and the Housing Finance Authority, among others.
His responsibilities include constructing and updating financial models, conducting risk analysis and assisting with negotiated and competitive sales.  He has constructed debt service models for the City of New York, the State of New York, LGAC, the State of Georgia and other PRAG clients.  For New York State Division of Budget (DOB), Mr. Evanchik provides continuous valuation and analysis of DOB’s swap portfolio in order to help advise on the available opportunities for DOB to continue to wind down its swap book.  He also maintains frequent contact with municipal swap pricing desks to keep abreast of current pricing levels regarding funding and credit charges as well as general market action.  Mr. Evanchik also provides valuation and analysis of other more complicated derivatives such as interest rate swaptions, caps, floors, total return swaps and inflation hedges.  A primary focus of this analysis is advising on the suitability, appropriateness and transparency of any derivative security for the client.
Prior to joining PRAG in 2004, Mr. Evanchik graduated from Columbia University with a MS in Financial Engineering. Mr. Evanchik also holds a BS in Systems Engineering from the University of Virginia.
Show moreShow less



Mark Gooding, Senior Managing Director
Certifications/Licenses: Series 50, Municipal Advisor Representative and
Series 65, Investment Advisor Representative
Mr. Gooding works in the firm’s New York office where he serves as project manager for several of the firm’s clients in the Northeast and Southeast, assisting clients with complex revenue bond financings and debt management practices to meet their needs. He also has an expertise in water and sewer and transportation finance and municipal reinvestment.
Mr. Gooding was employed previously by another financial advisory firm for ten years where he assisted large Northeast issuers with their financings, investments and ongoing advisory services. Mr. Gooding also worked in the New Jersey Treasurer’s Office, where he assisted with the issuance of over $2.0 billion of bonds.
Mr. Gooding received a B.A. in Economics from Ohio Wesleyan University and an M.B.A. in Finance from the State University of New York at Albany and is an Registered Investment Adviser’s Representative.
