Janet Lee, Senior Managing Director
Certifications/Licenses: Series 50, Municipal Advisor Representative
Ms. Lee has extensive experience in transportation financing including assisting major state transportation programs in privatization of highway projects. She also has worked on innovative financings to leverage federal transportation grants to states that have achieved high investment grade ratings without requiring pledges of state funding.
Prior to joining PRAG, Ms. Lee worked at Moody’s Investors Service in the public finance department, rating letter of credit supported bond issues. Ms. Lee formerly worked at the City of New York’s Office of Management and Budget for three years in the Tax Policy, Revenue Forecasting and Economic Analysis Task Force.
Ms. Lee holds a B.A. in Political Science from Cornell University, at which she was a Cornell-in-Washington scholar, and an M.B.A from New York University.
